How to choose the mattress and somier: women and men are looking for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for bed; what really gives its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the somier.
First and foremost, they must be perfectly complemented so that they can be adapted to the specific users.
During the election numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, state of health and gender of the owner.
It is also important the type of interior in which the mattress and summer are placed.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that is not usually heated, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them more frequently.
If the channels in the center are not properly aerated and, above, are on a firm foundation, they keep moisture inside.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Those who have spent a lot of time abroad often use a very tall mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower and harder surface.
“Almost all the hockey players who returned from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.”
"For their shattered shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who have problems with the nervous system, so they receive poor information from the joints and the skin," explains Sylva Hadamczikova, who specializes in cushioned furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This “miracle” works in a very simple way.
Optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not round like after a tough match.
Simply, he sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also acts as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of your feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example single rooms, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, you can apply a simple norm for calculating the width: when lying up your face, you should have your hands comfortably shrinked towards the elbows," counsels engineer Helena Prokopová, expert at Cechu čalouníků to dekoratéř, who has been dealing with the healthy sleep problem and ergonomics of the furniture for many years.
In double rooms, each needs its own sommer and mattress, so during the purchase you need to pay attention to matching the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the sockets at different heights, which is not always possible on all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with spring interior at least 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that fits the shapes and softens.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you sit on the mattress, the springs should certainly not be noticed," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of somier.
The fully quilted bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
The mattresses breathe poorly and can not wash their shell, which is done today often.
And since we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat each night, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress lifetime of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
Everything has a but.
That’s why sellers give a tip: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully take care of the cleaning and washing of the case, but better add a mattress protector that can be removed and washed easily.
Although mattress covers with zipper closure are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when they are opened they remain in two parts (something very important for washing and washing machine size!), their handling on the larger models (and by a single person) when lifting the mattress can look like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a suede, do you have a firm board?
Never!
As much for beds designed for one night visits.
However, you should do (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes on the board and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulable sheet sockets containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber) can be used, although a socket with a higher number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar area are reinforced and their rigidity can be regulated.
Articulable sheet sockets should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
This is a special attachment of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "roll" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is very important.
They are even remembered by the mattress manufacturers who, in the "male", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are cross-structured or tabled sockets with the so-called multi-torsion cushioning.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is lowered.
You should also note that even if you use the proper mattress and summer, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mullida"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow should hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles can be relaxed.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on the side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the shoulder brace or the softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses seem to have something to do with the original straw-filled mattresses.
Manufacturers continue to use, more and more often, natural materials or at least mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
Oil-based raw materials, with which the polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils, for example, castor or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
“Biologically, in the case of mattresses, it means that the center is made solely of materials of natural origin,” explains Petr Vasíček of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men are "cooled" with breeze vegetable extracts, so the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel warmer.
Favorites right now?
The mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various rigidities of cold foam and viscoelastic allow you to make mattresses from various areas that know perfectly where your head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who perform a therapeutic function usually have a lower VAT, since they are considered as healthcare means.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and sommers.
Sometimes you can approve the offers of manufacturers or sellers, who sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a memory foam attached to the case for 11,990 crowns.
The second is obtained for free.
The era of viscoelastic with an open cell structure and high density began with the "cosmic" material of Tempur.
It initially emerged as material for NASA, because during the takeoffs astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Consequently, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is used not only in mattresses, but also for sanitary devices, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use the Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents use people tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Anička Janatková.
For the time being, the device is the approximate size of a light box, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were afraid of the case of the missing Anička and began to inform about the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
“We’re all trying to tell each other that it’s not about spying, but another way to decrease the chances of a tragedy occurring,” says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I acknowledge that in certain cases such devices can be abused, for example if they are put in someone’s bag without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases.”
“Most customers actually buy it for safety reasons,” Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns about the fact that if the child does not want to carry it, he will simply throw it away.
“Even younger children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to prevent them from being controlled.”
“Earlier, parents trusted mobile phones enormously, but they could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” says Bočková.
In his opinion, it is controversial whether in the event of an attack such a device is really useful.
“If this is a prepared kidnapping, the author will virtually always check whether the child carries any kind of electronic device that can reveal their location.”
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices is spreading, it will also look for them, since their sale will certainly be done with a lot of advertising."
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack by a paedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to send the position regularly after a certain period of time."
"If it suffers damage, it will at least facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The most expensive devices have an inclination meter integrated, so if the person simply slips and remains immobile, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says Čech.
In their opinion, such a service can be obtained even with smartphones with navigation, in which only special software should be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment they are devices with a size similar to a lightbox or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they can be lost.
According to Pilin of Macro Weil, for that reason, tests are currently being carried out on devices that resemble a digital clock.
"In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential aggressor may not identify the device."
"Or identify it after a certain time, which can save the police time," he adds.
Even though tracking devices are carried on the wrist or hanging, they will still use the same technology that is used for vehicle tracking.
This is the position check with a GPS system (which is used in the usual navigation in the car) combined with the function of a mobile phone that communicates the current position.
The army has enough mechs to surround all of the Czech Republic, but it only lasts two years.
The Czech army bought 445 kilometers of mecha to fire explosives.
Last year, the Ministry of Defense added 224 kilometers of mecha to its arsenal.
Therefore, they have stocks for 225 years.
The problem is that the useful life of the wick is two years, four at most.
The army bought the explosive mesh from the STV Group, a.s. for forty million crowns.
The General’s staff responded to MF DNES justifying the purchase of such a huge amount of mecha by saying that soldiers need 60 kilometers of mecha per year for training manoeuvres.
According to the calculations of the army pyrotechnics, with whom MF DNES was contacted, it is decided, however, that in such cases, such manoeuvres should be carried out with frequent use of explosives every year also all generals, high-command officers, and even secretaries and cleaners.
They did not want exempted either Minister of Defense Alexandr Vondr and Army Captain Vlastimil Picek.
Only in this way could it be justified for the army to spend sixty kilometers of mecha.
Such a length is equal to 25,000 explosions.
Even so, the army would have enough stocks for more than ten years.
If, on the contrary, as experts say, for the initial training of each new professional arrives with a maximum of two meters of mecha, the army would have with the new purchase (even adding the consumption of the units of engineers or specials) sufficient stocks for the 225 mentioned above.
The soldiers of the Quick Response Brigade complained personally to Minister Vondra recently because they say they barely have ammunition for various weapons, so even money-based shooting practices are limited.
And let’s not talk about the lack of underwear.
"I can also not understand that such amounts of mecha are repeatedly purchased from us."
“But it’s their decision and they’ll undoubtedly know why they’re acting like that.”
“For us, the army is a good customer that we, as a company, try to satisfy,” admits Jan Děcký, commercial director of STV Group.
Defense Ministry spokesman Jan Pejšek defends the hundreds of kilometers of mecha, also saying he will have stocks of this "munition" for at least ten years.
However, Jan Děcký of STV Group indicates that the mesh only has a lifespan of four years and, in the case of pyrotechnic products for the army or the police, two years.
"If it is stored in perfect conditions, it can last up to four," says one of the soldiers who, due to the possible criticism of the army, does not want to give his name.
After the end of its life, each ammunition must be carefully checked to see if it remains reliable and will not harm the soldiers.
But these trials are not free and require additional investment.
Another argument from the Ministry is that, by buying 445 kilometers of mecha, it got a discount.
"They cost us 60% less than last year's 244 kilometer order," said spokesman Pejšek of the Defense Ministry's shopping center.
Just to compare: the annual consumption of mesh from the police pyrotechnics, who eliminate the ammunition from World War II or left by the Soviet army, has not exceeded 1,500 meters for years.
In addition, the police always ask only the fair amount to deplete the ammunition before its useful life ends.
It was decided for safety reasons for pyrotechnicians and, in addition, in the meantime, more modern and reliable types of mesh can be obtained.
The Ministry is already experiencing clear difficulties in finishing tens of thousands of tons of ammunition from the time of the Warsaw Pact, when the Czechoslovak army of two hundred thousand people was preparing for a campaign on the Rhine.
According to the pyrotechnicians with whom MF DNES spoke, after a couple of years the following problem will arise with the current one: hundreds of kilometers of old mecha, which is now being bought "cheap".
So far I'm still living from the contacts I got thanks to the contest
Winning the "Businessman of the Year" contest helped Lukáš Pytloun sell his hotel franchises.
In the last edition, the 28-year-old entrepreneur Lukáš Pytloun of Liberec won the "Entrepreneur of the Year" contest.
His success story seems to be taken from a movie.
Lukáš Pytloun loved traveling.
Abroad he realized that Liberec needed quality accommodation at a good price.
With the savings he gathered with seasonal jobs abroad and a bank credit he bought a half-ruined house composed of five floors.
Given that he was still studying his third year in college, he was really brave.
“At present, the value for money ratio of the accommodation in our area has pushed me to do something about it,” says Lukáš Pytloun.
He began renting the first rebuilt floor to foreign workers.
All the income he earned invested them back in the building, which gradually turned into a 54-room pension.
Since then, in seven years in the business, he has gradually managed to open in Liberec four guesthouses, two stylish restaurants and two hotels with a total capacity of around 300 in all accommodation categories.
The most comfortable of all was, until recently, the four-star design hotel Pytloun.
However, this year it opened another of the same quality.
"We have just signed a contract with a hotel in Ostrov or Tisé, to which we have sold our franchise concept, and other people are showing interest in a Pytloun franchise," the entrepreneur said last year.
“This sale of licenses for the opening of hotels helped greatly by winning the ‘Entrepreneur of the Year’ competition,” says Pytloun.
The victory increased his fame and popularity in Liberec as well as in the surrounding area.
“People recognized me on the street, they still congratulated me often and, I must say, it was very nice,” he recalls.
It certainly recommends to everyone who wants to try some company to participate in the contest.
But he believes that it is not necessary to win, but that participation is already beneficial.
He claims that, so far, he continues to live from the contacts and acquaintances that, without the contest, he might not have obtained.
"With some people I met thanks to the contest I have started collaborating regularly."
The fame associated with success, in his opinion, also included employees,
In total about seventy.
“I’ve seen them show greater loyalty and they’re proud to be involved in something that gained overall recognition.”
“It’s not, much less, my own personal success, but it’s the result of the hard work of the entire team.”
"It is only my name that appears on the front floor," says Lukáš Pytloun modestly today.
I wish my successor a quieter year than we have had at Farmet.
The euphoria for victory soon dissolved by the impact of the crisis.
