“It must offset at any price the lack of investors in the market and act in such a way that it prevents a marked increase in returns paid by the most fragile states,” an important bond manager said yesterday.
Because, if interest rates are clouded, states will have even more difficulty reducing their indebtedness, or even stabilizing it.
